ABOUT US




Senior Team
Advisers







Keiren Charles, CFA
Chairman and Chief Investment Officer

											Mr. Charles directs the investment strategy of CLC. He was previously Co-Head of Corporate Finance, South-East Asia at Credit Suisse, leading landmark business purchases, divestments and security issuances across countries and industries.
		    						

		    							Mr. Charles’ investment approach involves investing in businesses globally on a concentrated basis, based on fundamental and other analysis. Investments have predominantly been in the technology, internet, healthcare, consumer, real estate and financial services sectors. His investing experience is global, with particular experience in Asia.
		    						

MORE 


											Mr Charles previously also worked in investment banking at Deutsche Bank and practiced law focusing on mergers and acquisitions at Freehills (now Herbert Smith Freehills). He formerly taught classes in business finance, corporate finance and quantitative methods at the University of Melbourne in Australia, where he and Dr Liu were also researchers in the area of economics and finance.
		    						

		    							Mr. Charles is a Chartered Financial Analyst and a qualified barrister and solicitor of the Supreme Court of Victoria, Australia. He holds a double degree in Commerce (Honours in Finance) and Law from the University of Melbourne.
		    						




Lim Shueh Yung
Managing Director

											Ms. Lim was previously a fund manager at the Government of Singapore Investment Corporation (GIC), investing in global securities within GIC Real Estate, focused on the Asia-Pacific region and concentrated strategic investments. She also worked in investment banking at UBS and practiced corporate law at Allens Arthur Robinson (now Allens Linklaters), advising on business purchases, divestments and security issuances across the region.
		    						

MORE 


											Ms. Lim’s experience includes the consumer, healthcare, financial services, real estate, telecommunications/media and infrastructure sectors. She previously taught classes in accounting at the University of Melbourne in Australia, and was also a researcher in global securities market regulations and corporate governance for the Centre for Corporate Law and Securities Regulation.
		    						

		    							Ms. Lim holds a double degree in Commerce and Law (Honours) from the University of Melbourne, where she was recipient of the Blake Dawson Waldron and Corrs Chambers Westgarth law prizes. She is a former ASEAN Scholar and a qualified barrister and solicitor of the Supreme Court of Victoria, Australia.
		    						




Dr. Raymond Liu
Research

											Dr. Liu is a member of CLC's research team, and is also currently tenured as an Associate Professor in Finance at the Australian National University. He is the author of numerous academic finance studies and co-author of the book “Inframarginal Economics”, which he co-wrote with the late Professor Xiaokai Yang – two-time nominee for the Nobel Prize in Economics.
		    						

MORE 


											Dr. Liu’s research interests are broad and diverse, ranging across the areas of asset pricing, quantitative finance, empirical and theoretical market microstructure, microeconomic theory, political economy and the study of the insights of Adam Smith’s division of labour and specialisation on increasing returns.
		    						

		    						Dr. Liu holds a PhD in Finance from the University of Melbourne, Australia, as well as a Masters in Commerce (Honours), postgraduate Diploma in Finance and Bachelor of Commerce from the University of Melbourne.
		    						












