Charles-Lim Capital Ltd Buys NetEase Inc, Sells ICICI Bank, Baidu Inc, Ctrip.com International


May 11, 2017, 08:38:02 AM EDT
By insider, GuruFocus









































Shutterstock photo


Charles-Lim Capital LtdNew Purchases: NTES ,Reduced Positions: BIDU , CTRP , VIPS, JD,Sold Out:IBN,For the details of Charles-Lim Capital Ltd's stock buys and sells, go to http://www.gurufocus.com/StockBuy.php?GuruName=Charles-Lim+Capital+LtdThese are the top 5 holdings of Charles-Lim Capital LtdVipshop Holdings Ltd ( VIPS ) - 7,884,886 shares, 29.5% of the total portfolio. Shares reduced by 3.31%JD.com Inc ( JD ) - 3,346,980 shares, 29.2% of the total portfolio. Shares reduced by 1.02%HDFC Bank Ltd ( HDB ) - 924,138 shares, 19.49% of the total portfolio. Shares added by 0.04%Baidu Inc ( BIDU ) - 361,712 shares, 17.5% of the total portfolio. Shares reduced by 30.22%NetEase Inc ( NTES ) - 28,621 shares, 2.28% of the total portfolio. New PositionNew Purchase: NetEase Inc ( NTES )Charles-Lim Capital Ltd initiated holdings in NetEase Inc. The purchase prices were between $218.16 and $305.06, with an estimated average price of $269.25. The stock is now traded at around $279.05. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 2.28%. The holdings were 28,621 shares as of 2017-03-31.Sold Out: ICICI Bank Ltd (IBN)Charles-Lim Capital Ltd sold out the holdings in ICICI Bank Ltd. The sale prices were between $7.45 and $8.78, with an estimated average price of $8.21.Warning! GuruFocus has detected 3 Warning Signs with NTES. Click here to check it out.NTES 15-Year Financial DataThe intrinsic value of NTESPeter Lynch Chart of NTESPremium MembersThis article first appeared on GuruFocus .



